-- Suncor Oil Sands Refinery in Edmonton Shutting Down After Power Failure
-- Aaron Clark
-- 2010-06-30T11:05:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-30/suncor-oil-sands-refinery-in-edmonton-shutting-down-after-power-failure.html

          
          
             Suncor Energy Inc .’s Edmonton
 refinery  in Canada was struck by a power failure late yesterday
and was in the process of shutting down, according to a message
left on a community hotline at 8:10 p.m. local time on June 29.  
 The plant processes oil sands-based feedstocks, according
to the company’s  website . The refinery, which can process
134,900 barrels of crude a day, produces mostly gasoline and
distillate fuels for markets in Western Canada.  
